7}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's C4 4000m individual pursuit\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games debutant led reigning champion Jozef Metelka by around six seconds and looked certain to top the podium.\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 626, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 553, \"end\": 558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jozef_Kroner\", \"score\": 0.9999999804194888, \"rank\": 1.9580694058387993e-08, \"text\": \"Jozef\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jozef_Kroner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jozef_Kroner\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Games debutant\", \"from\": 512, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"around six seconds\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 588}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 615, \"to\": 625}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he painfully fell with just over two laps to go inParisbefore being helped from the track in clear discomfort.\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 742, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just over two laps\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"the track\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"clear discomfort\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 741}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite not finishing, the 20-year-old defiantly raised his arms to a sympathetic crowd and was awarded the silver medal after Slovakian rival Metelka capitalised on the shock incident to power on and retain his crown.\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his arms\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 808}, {\"ngram\": \"a sympathetic crowd\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 831}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver medal\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 864}, {\"ngram\": \"Slovakian rival Metelka\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"the shock incident\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 928}, {\"ngram\": \"his crown\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 961}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This happened last probably when the T-rex was around, I feel massively lucky,\\\" said 37-year-old Metelka.\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the T-rex\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1007}, {\"ngram\": \"37-year-old Metelka\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The luck is like from here to the Eiffel Tower and back, it's just indescribable.\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The luck\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1119}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Cleary, he's a better rider, he's stronger, I was five seconds down - you do not recover from there.\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1257, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a better rider\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You can try to upset the rhythm, you can try to play the game and maybe something happens, whether that helped, whatever that was, this was luck that I do not comprehend.\\\"\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1431, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rhythm\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1291}, {\"ngram\": \"the game\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1321}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1341}, {\"ngram\": \"whatever\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"luck\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1404}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Double world champion Atkinson had taken the world record from his opponent in the heats and his domination continued until the untimely tumble.\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Double world champion Atkinson\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"the world record\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1490}, {\"ngram\": \"his opponent\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"the heats\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"his domination\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1540}, {\"ngram\": \"the untimely tumble\", \"from\": 1557, \"to\": 1576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His agony came just two days after British team-mateKadeena Coxcrashed out of the women's C4-5 time trial champion at the other end of the velodrome.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1728, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"His agony\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's C4-5 time trial champion\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"the other end\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1710}, {\"ngram\": \"the velodrome\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1727}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Atkinson, who has cerebral palsy,ADHDand is autistic, recovered sufficiently to take his place on the podium following treatment in the track centre.\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1879, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Atkinson\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"cerebral palsy\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1762}, {\"ngram\": \"his place\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1824}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1838}, {\"ngram\": \"treatment\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1858}, {\"ngram\": \"the track centre\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Supporters in the stands chanted 'Archie, Archie, Archie' during the medal ceremony.\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1915, \"end\": 1921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\", \"score\": 0.8367693523363187, \"rank\": 0.16803119298970723, \"text\": \"Archie\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\"}, {\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\", \"score\": 0.8367693523363187, \"rank\": 0.16803119298970723, \"text\": \"Archie\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\"}, {\"begin\": 1931, \"end\": 1937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archie_Comics\", \"score\": 0.8367693523363187, \"rank\": 0.16803